Rating: 4
this was incredibly easy and incredibly delicious. i didn't have any shallots so i diced two small yellow onions and used them instead (more than called for but i love onion). i used the zest and juice from half of a lemon and a can of great northern beans. i didn't have watercress, so we just ate it at room temp on boston lettuce with crusty baguette. i think it's one of the fastest and best recipes on epicurious: ready in practically minutes, virtually no clean-up, and a total crowd pleaser. will def. make again when in a time crunch.

